{"timestamp": "2025-12-11 18:09:30.122876", "event": "llm_end", "text": "**Network‑Level Diagnostic Report**\n\n| Item | Observation | Interpretation | Anomaly / Root Cause |\n|------|-------------|-----------------|----------------------|\n| **Host connectivity** | `pc_0_0` → `pc_0_1` ping returns *Destination Net Unreachable* from 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0). | Leaf_router_0_0 has no route to 10.0.1.0/24. | Host unreachable due to missing routing information. |\n| **Leaf‑router BGP tables** | leaf_router_0_0: only 10.0.0.0/24; leaf_router_0_1: only 10.0.1.0/24. | Each leaf advertises only its own subnet and does not learn the other leaf’s subnet. | BGP sessions with the opposite leaf are not exchanging routes. |\n| **Spine‑router BGP tables** | spine_router_0_0: 10.0.0.0/24 via leaf_router_0_0; no 10.0.1.0/24. <br>spine_router_0_1: two paths for 10.0.0.0/24, still no 10.0.1.0/24. | Spines are not receiving or advertising the 10.0.1.0/24 network. | BGP peering with leaf_router_0_1 is broken. |\n| **AS numbers in configuration** | <br>leaf_router_0_0: AS 65200 (correct). <br>leaf_router_0_1: AS 65801 (incorrect). <br>spine_router_0_0 expects leaf_router_0_1 AS 65201; spine_router_0_1 expects leaf_router_0_1 AS 65201. | AS mismatch between leaf_router_0_1 and both spines. | BGP session establishment fails, preventing route exchange. |\n| **Neighbor definitions** | <br>leaf_router_0_1 neighbors 172.16.0.6 (remote‑AS 65100) and 172.16.0.10 (remote‑AS 65101). <br>spine_router_0_0 expects remote‑AS 65200 for leaf_router_0_0 and remote‑AS 65201 for leaf_router_0_1. | The remote‑AS values in the spine configs do not match the AS of leaf_router_0_1. | No BGP session is formed with leaf_router_0_1. |\n| **Super‑spine view** | super_spine_router_0 advertises routes from both spines, but spines still lack leaf_router_0_1 routes. | Super‑spine is healthy; the problem is confined to the leaf‑spine links. | Mis‑configured AS numbers on leaf_router_0_1. |\n\n### Summary of Findings\n\n1. **Ping failure** – The only reachable host is `pc_0_0`; `pc_0_1` is unreachable because leaf_router_0_0 has no route to its subnet.\n2. **BGP tables** – All routers only know their own /24 networks; no cross‑subnet routes are present.\n3. **Spine‑leaf peering** – The BGP sessions between the spines and `leaf_router_0_1` are not established due to an AS number mismatch.\n4. **AS configuration error** – `leaf_router_0_1` is configured with AS 65801, while the spines expect AS 65201 for that leaf. Consequently, the spine‑leaf sessions fail and the 10.0.1.0/24 network is never advertised into the fabric.\n\n### Root Cause\n\nA **mis‑configured Autonomous System number** on `leaf_router_0_1` (and the corresponding remote‑AS values on the spines) prevents BGP session establishment. Without a valid BGP session, the spine routers never receive the 10.0.1.0/24 advertisement, leaving `leaf_router_0_0` (and the entire fabric) unable to reach `pc_0_1`.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Correct `leaf_router_0_1`’s BGP AS to **65201** (the same AS used by the spines for that leaf).\n- Update the spine neighbor definitions to match the leaf’s AS (or vice‑versa) so that the BGP sessions can be established.\n- Verify that all BGP sessions are up (`show ip bgp summary` or `show ip bgp neighbors` on each router).\n- Once sessions are established, confirm that each leaf advertises its subnet and that the spines propagate those routes to the rest of the fabric.\n- Re‑run the ping test to ensure connectivity between `pc_0_0` and `pc_0_1`.\n\nOnce the AS numbers are aligned, the BGP tables should populate with both subnets, and the hosts will become reachable.", "generation_info": {"model": "gpt-oss:20b", "created_at": "2025-12-11T18:09:29.619624107Z", "done": true, "done_reason": "stop", "total_duration": 33492807962, "load_duration": 68444683, "prompt_eval_count": 6560, "prompt_eval_duration": 879418814, "eval_count": 3222, "eval_duration": 30984659359, "model_name": "gpt-oss:20b"}, "i